'''Jonas Bonnier''' (born 1963) is a Swedish author who has published 8 novels. His latest work, ''The Helicopter Heist'' about the [[Västberga helicopter robbery]], has been sold to 34 territories. It is his first attempt in the suspense novel category. The film- and TV-rights were acquired by Netflix and Jake Gyllenhalls production company Nine Stories. Bonnier was President of the [[Bonnier Group]] from 1 January 2008<ref>{{cite news | title=Bengt Braun avgår som vd för Bonnier AB | url=http://www.dn.se/ekonomi/bengt-braun-avgar-som-vd-for-bonnier-ab-1.554720 | archive-url=https://archive.is/20120802200237/http://www.dn.se/ekonomi/bengt-braun-avgar-som-vd-for-bonnier-ab-1.554720 | dead-url=yes | archive-date=2012-08-02 | publisher=[[Dagens Nyheter]] | date=2007-10-12 | language=Swedish | accessdate=13 February 2010 }}</ref> until May 2013. He is a member of the [[Bonnier family]].


