{{Infobox person | name = Laszlo Bock<!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name --> | image = Laszlo Bock 2014.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = Laszlo Bock in 2014 | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name --> | birth_date = <!-- {{Birth date and age|1972|October|31}} or {{Birth-date and age|birth date†}} --> | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|death date†|birth date†}} --> | death_place = | nationality = American | notable_works = Work Rules!: Insights from Inside Google That Will Transform How You Live and Lead | other_names = | alma_mater = Pomona College (BA), [[Yale School of Management]], MBA<ref>[http://som.yale.edu/news/news/laszlo-bock-99-vp-people-operations-google Laszlo Bock '99, VP People Operations, Google]</ref> | occupation = | years_active = | known_for = Former Senior Vice President of People Operations at Google }}
'''Laszlo Bock''' is an American businessman who is co-founder and CEO of Humu.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.humu.com}}</ref> He was formerly the Senior Vice President of People Operations at [[Google, Inc]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.google.com/about/company/facts/management/ |title=Management team – Company – Google |publisher=Google.com |date= |accessdate=2015-05-04}}</ref> Prior to joining Google, Bock served in [[Executive (management)|executive]] roles {{which|date=July 2018}} at [[General Electric]], as a management consultant at [[McKinsey & Company]], and in various roles at startups, nonprofits, and in acting. During his time at Google{{Citation needed|date=October 2018|reason=years}}, the company has been named the Best Company to Work for over 30 times around the world and received over 100 awards as a top employer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.workrules.net/ |accessdate=April 28, 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150421082806/https://www.workrules.net/ |archivedate=April 21, 2015 }}</ref> In 2010, Bock was named "Human Resources Executive of the Year" by ''HR Resources Magazine''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marketwired.com/press-release/googles-laszlo-bock-named-2010-hr-executive-of-the-year-1328227.htm |title=Google's Laszlo Bock Named 2010 HR Executive of the Year |publisher=Marketwired.com |date=2010-10-01 |accessdate=2015-05-04}}</ref> He resigned his position at Google in 2016, though stayed on as an adviser to CEO [[Sundar Pichai]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=D'Onfro|first1=Jillian|title=The man who molded Google's culture over the last 10 years just stepped down|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/laszlo-bock-steps-down-as-head-of-hr-at-google|publisher=Business Insider|accessdate=4 January 2017}}</ref>
On April 7, 2015, Bock published his first book, ''[[The New York Times]]'' bestseller<ref>{{cite web|last=Taylor |first=Ihsan |url=https://www.nytimes.com/best-sellers-books/2015-04-26/advice-how-to-and-miscellaneous/list.html |title=Best Sellers - ''The New York Times'' |publisher=Nytimes.com |date= |accessdate=2015-05-04}}</ref> and ''Wall Street Journal'' bestseller,<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=M6idBAAAQBAJ|title=Work Rules!: Insights from Inside Google That Will Transform How You Live and Lead|last=Bock|first=Laszlo|date=2015-04-07|publisher=Grand Central Publishing|isbn=9781455554805|language=en}}</ref> ''Work Rules!'', a practical guide to help people find meaning in work and improve the way they live and lead.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.hachettebookgroup.com/titles/laszlo-bock/work-rules/9781455554799/ |title=Work Rules! |publisher=Hachettebookgroup.com |date= |accessdate=2015-05-04}}</ref> He has been on several book tours around the world, often accompanied by his family.
He was born in 1972 in [[Romania]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hreonline.com/HRE/view/story.jhtml?id=533322196 |title=Building a New Breed}}</ref>
== HUMU Culture ==
Laszlo Bock along with two former Google executives Wayne Crosby and Jessie Wisdom founded HUMU, a startup devoted to making work more beneficial for people in different industries. Their main objective of the company is to employ Behavioral Change Technology in ensuring that employees are happier in their respective jobs. The technology has become popular because it establishes a viable technique to increase adoption of positive modifications in behavior<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.productiveedge.com/blog/developing-effective-behavioral-change-technology/|title=Developing Effective Behavioral Change Technology - Productive Edge Blog|date=2015-04-09|work=Productive Edge Blog|access-date=2018-05-27|language=en-US}}</ref>. The company’s strategies are anchored on novel innovations in machine erudition and many years of conducting scientific research on human behavior. Business Insider was able to interview Bock and Crosby regarding the hiring process at HUMU. The co-founders pointed out one quality that makes a certain candidate more prominent and that is the capability to convey his or her own story. This trait is just as essential as technical proficiency. Applicants get the chance to present their personal history and experiences to the interviewer<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/ex-google-employees-humu-hiring-2018-5|title=Google's former HR exec has a new startup — and he says technical skills alone aren't enough to get hired|work=Business Insider|access-date=2018-05-27}}</ref>. An article published in Forbes.com quoted HUMU’s mission statement as “''Making work better everywhere through machine learning, science, and a little bit of love.''” <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/vickyvalet/2018/05/01/after-a-year-of-secrecy-laszlo-bock-and-wayne-crosby-break-their-silence-on-humu/#143e929c1c94|title=After A Year Of Secrecy, Laszlo Bock And Wayne Crosby Break Their Silence On Humu|last=Valet|first=Vicky|work=Forbes|access-date=2018-05-27|language=en}}</ref>.
Laszlo Bock was scheduled to deliver a Keynote Speech at 2018 CEO Leadership Summit<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://chiefexecutive.net/laszlo-bock-on-the-future-of-leadership/|title=Former Google People Chief Laszlo Bock On The Future Of Leadership|last=Bigman|first=Dan|date=2018-03-12|work=ChiefExecutive.net|access-date=2018-05-27|language=en-US}}</ref>.
